    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-03-31T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-03-31T10:00:00-05:00" n="970"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d970">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/9507: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-31T18:00:00+03:00"
                            >March 31, 1941—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 1—7:38 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>87. In conversation with our Military Attaché yesterday Von Papen<note n="78"
                        xml:id="d970fn78">Franz von Papen, German Ambassador in Turkey.</note> made
                    the statement that if Yugoslavia will not join the new order peacefully Germany
                    will compel her to do so by military force in order to prevent the British and
                    Americans forcing her into the other camp.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
